    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/9–244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé Near the Greek Government in Exile</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02">September 2,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received September 2—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Greek 281. The EAM representatives reached Cairo August 31. Following Ministers
                    were sworn in this noon: Svolos Finance with Angelopoulos Under Minister;
                    Askoutsis Communications; Tsirimokos National Economy; Porphyrogennis Labor and
                    Zevghos Agriculture.</p>
                <p>Repeated to AmPolAd<note n="16" xml:id="d140fn16">American Political Adviser,
                        Staff of the Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean, with headquarters at
                        Caserta, Italy.</note> Caserta as number 40.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
